Text: What we've done this week
The past week we got round to three team meetings, one with Jeremiah and progress with image segmentation algorithms and UI features.
The good
Overall we have done a much better job of communicating with each other and people taking initiative to get tasks done.
Everyone seems to be able to work well with each other to discuss ideas that they have.
We had a good session on Friday to reflect on the work we had done as a team.
This type of meeting will be useful to repeat each week to try and improve as we go along in the project.
Toto has been doing a good job working on the UI with plenty of ideas to address problems we will need to combat going forward.
Rara has also done a good job exploring some image pre-processing that may come in useful for refining our segmentation.
Nene has been doing a good job of being active in operating our team meetings and working on the front end portion of the project.
Things to improve as a team

The things we will need to improve on for next week were addressed on our Friday meeting and this included keeping Jeremiah updated on progress throughout the week, prioritising features that we will need to implement given the time frame and taking more initiative to contact each other when solving problems.

We will address the prioritising of features at the start of next week, going over everything that may need to be implemented and having low fidelity prototypes ready to show the users at the anatomy department.
We have also decided our meetings times for next week to make sure we can discuses any issues that we may have.
I feel we are working well and I hope we only need to maintain our focus on what we can improve, as opposed to solving major interpersonal issues that can occur during group work.
Things I could do betterI completed work to process our images in the back end, but I feel I could have done a better job of learning what was happening on the front end of the project.
To help address this I will run through code for the UI that has been done so far to see how everything has been connected together.
Goals for next week.
The goals for the upcoming week are to get a meeting with the anatomy department, as we weren't able to secure one last week.
We are also hoping to integrate more features into the UI and play around with the background algorithms to refine the segmentation.
General thoughts.
I felt we've had a productive week overall, everyone has been taking ownership of tasks in the project which has made things quite smooth.
My frustration so far just has been figuring how to do things, butÂ  these problems are pretty normal so I'm happy we haven't had much team drama.
I do worry about some of my team mates putting too much pressure on themselves to solve things quickly and have tried to be encouraging when going they are going through difficulty implementing code.
I also sometimes wonder maybe I'm being too easy on some of my teammates because they are my friends, but I feel I've treated everyone fairly to do a good job on the project.
So far I have learnt that working with people you get along with and take initiative helps the experience in the project tremendously.
It has been fun so far and I hope we can continue the good work going forward.
